<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

<p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 29 July 2025</p>

<p>
    The Hervey Players respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information.
    This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our booking system.
</p>

<h3>Information We Collect</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email address, and booking details (show date, number of seats).</li>
    <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> Currently no credit card data is stored; payments will be processed securely via Stripe (future implementation).</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Basic analytics (page views, form submissions) to improve user experience.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How We Use Your Information</h3>
<ul>
    <li>To process and confirm your theatre bookings.</li>
    <li>To send booking confirmations or e-tickets.</li>
    <li>To notify you of changes to show times or cancellations.</li>
    <li>To improve our services and website functionality.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Data Sharing</h3>
<p>
    We do not sell or rent your personal data. Information is only shared with trusted service providers
    (e.g., payment processors) as required to complete your booking.
</p>

<h3>Data Retention</h3>
<p>
    Booking records are retained for up to 12 months for reporting and auditing purposes. You may request deletion earlier by contacting us.
</p>

<h3>Your Rights</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Access and correct your personal data.</li>
    <li>Request deletion of your booking information.</li>
    <li>Opt out of communications (other than essential booking notifications).</li>
</ul>

